  "prompt": "How do I know viewers of my Facebook profile?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, Facebook does not provide a direct way to see exactly who has viewed your profile. While some people mistakenly believe there are apps or methods to do this, Facebook does not offer such a feature. Here are a few things to know:\n\n1. Profile views tracking is not possible on Facebook\n2. Any app or website claiming to show profile visitors is likely a scam\n3. You can see:\n- Who has liked your posts\n- Who has commented on your posts\n- Who views your public posts\n- Friend requests and interactions\n\nThe best way to see who's engaging with your content is to check your post interactions and notifications.",
